calamares-settings-foundry-linux (1.0.22) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Fix slideshow text clipping (take 6 — ACTUAL root cause). The clipped text
    was never in the QML caption that takes 1–5 kept editing: it is baked into
    the 800x440 slide PNGs. fillMode was Image.PreserveAspectCrop, which scaled
    each slide to FILL the taller installer pane and cropped ~77 px off each
    side — clipping the first glyph of every heading ("Where"->"Vhere"). Switch
    to Image.PreserveAspectFit (whole slide shown, dark backdrop hides the
    letterbox) and remove the now-redundant QML caption (the PNG already carries
    the heading + body). Takes 1–5 were fixing the wrong element entirely.

 -- Will Norris <wbnorris@gmail.com>  Tue, 09 Jun 2026 23:30:00 +0700

