calamares-settings-foundry-linux (1.0.15) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Fix mount.conf: options must be YAML arrays (["bind"] not "bind") —
    Calamares mount module schema validation rejects scalar options, causing
    the entire extraMounts block to be silently skipped and grub-install to
    fail with error code 1 (no block devices in target /dev).
  * Fix mount.conf: remove extraMountsEfi (not a valid schema key in
    Calamares 3.3 mount module) — merge efivarfs entry into extraMounts
    with efi: true per the actual module schema.

 -- Will Norris <wbnorris@gmail.com>  Sun, 08 Jun 2026 23:15:00 +0700

calamares-settings-foundry-linux (1.0.14) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Add mount.conf: bind-mount /dev, /dev/pts, /proc, /sys, /run, and
    /sys/firmware/efi/efivars (EFI only) into the target chroot via
    extraMounts/extraMountsEfi. Without this Calamares runs grub-install in a
    chroot with no block devices in /dev, causing "cannot find a device for
    /boot/efi" and aborting the bootloader step.
  * Fix packages.conf: set skip_if_no_internet=false so the live-package
    removal (calamares, live-boot, etc.) always runs even when Calamares
    hasInternet detection is inconclusive.

 -- Will Norris <wbnorris@gmail.com>  Sun, 08 Jun 2026 10:00:00 +0700

calamares-settings-foundry-linux (1.0.13) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Fix partition.conf: Calamares 3.3 PartitionLayout::init() requires both
    "name" and "size" as mandatory keys per entry — without "name" it silently
    switches to a default layout that creates no root partition, so unsquashfs
    extracts to the live tmpfs and fails with exit 1. Add efi: block so
    Calamares sizes the EFI partition correctly (300 MiB).
  * Add bootloader.conf: set efiBootLoader=grub so Calamares runs grub-install
    after filesystem copy. Without this the bootloader module skips entirely
    and the installed system has no bootloader.
  * Fix settings.conf: move packages before bootloader so grub-efi-amd64 is
    present in the target before grub-install runs.
  * Fix slideshow clipping: increase windowSize 800px→1100px; replace fixed
    800×440 root Item dimensions with anchors.fill: parent.

 -- Will Norris <wbnorris@gmail.com>  Fri, 06 Jun 2026 13:30:00 +0700

calamares-settings-foundry-linux (1.0.12) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Add partition.conf: set defaultFileSystemType=ext4 and initialSwapChoice=none.
    Without defaultFileSystemType, Calamares leaves root fs type as "unknown" and
    auto-partitioner creates only EFI + swap with no root partition, causing
    unsquashfs to fail (exit 1, no output) at the "Unpack filesystems" step.

 -- Will Norris <wbnorris@gmail.com>  Fri, 06 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0700

calamares-settings-foundry-linux (1.0.11) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Fix unpackfsc.conf: remove unpack: list wrapper — CppJobModule calls
    setConfigurationMap() once with the full config map; getString(map, "source")
    returns empty when source is nested under unpack:, logging "Skipping item with
    bad source data" and returning ok() without extracting. Flat format only:
    source/sourcefs/destination at top level.

 -- Will Norris <wbnorris@gmail.com>  Thu, 05 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0700

calamares-settings-foundry-linux (1.0.10) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Fix unpackfsc.conf: change destination from "" to "/" — empty destination
    triggers "Skipping item with empty destination" in UnpackFSCJob::setConfigurationMap
    (the job silently returns ok() without extracting). Calamares::System::targetPath("/")
    resolves to rootMountPoint, so "/" is the correct value for "install root".

 -- Will Norris <wbnorris@gmail.com>  Thu, 05 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0700

calamares-settings-foundry-linux (1.0.9) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Switch Calamares unpack module from unpackfs (Python, rsync) to unpackfsc
    (C++, unsquashfs) — eliminates rsync RERR_FILEIO (error 11) during
    installation. unpackfsc uses UnsquashRunner directly instead of
    mount + rsync, so xattr-related rsync failures cannot occur.
  * Add unpackfsc.conf (mirrors unpackfs.conf config format).

